race.comment: SILKY SETH (9) was specked at double-figure odds on debut and ran up to that support with a good second placing. With the benefit of that experience, an extra 100m and a lovely draw he deserves to be considered the testing material. ANTALIAN (11) has been racing well and is close to a win, the latest effort a solid third at Kyneton over 1454m. Becoming costly but racing too consistently to dismiss. HATALOOK (13) came home soundly to finish fourth when resuming over 1170m at Wangaratta last time out. Takes on a tougher assignment this time but she is right in this. REDCLOUD (8) three-year-old gelding who's form on either side of a spell has been very ordinary. Lane goes on and watch the market with him.
